6 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 4.1-01-21 of the North Dakota Century Code is
7 amended and reenacted as follows:
8 4.1-01-21. Federal environmental law impact review fund - Continuing appropriation -
9 Investments.
10 1. The federal environmental law impact review fund consists of:
11 a. Any moneys appropriated or transferred for the purposes set forth in section
12 4.1-01-19; and
13 b. Any gifts, grants, and donations forwarded to the commissioner for the purposes
14 set forth in section 4.1-01-19.
15 2. All moneys in the federal environmental law impact review fund are appropriated to the
16 commissioner on a continuing basis for the purposes set forth in section 4.1-01-19.
17 The commissioner may invest moneys in the fund under the supervision of the state
18 investment board pursuant to chapter 21 - 10 .
19 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Section 4.1-01-21.1 of the North Dakota Century Code is
20 amended and reenacted as follows:
21 4.1-01-21.1. Environmental impact mitigation fund - Report to legislative
22 management - Continuing appropriation - Investments.
23 1. There is created in the state treasury the environmental impact mitigation fund. The
24 fund consists of all moneys deposited in the fund under section 49-22-09.2. All
